GphReport: Circuit Dark

Product Overview

The Pitch: A high-precision, technical reporting dashboard for university hardware research groups to submit, review, and track weekly progress. It replaces fragmented spreadsheets with a centralized, immutable record of engineering milestones, hardware specs, and meeting attendance.

For: Hardware engineering students, project managers, and faculty advisors who need structured visibility into weekly R&D cycles.

Device: desktop

Design Direction: Circuit Dark — a brutalist, technical aesthetic mimicking modern IDEs and PCB design software. Deep charcoal backgrounds, 1px sharp borders, electric cyan accents, and monospaced data visualization.

Inspired by: Linear, Altium Designer, VS Code



Screens





Auth (Login/Register): Terminal-style entry point for member access and registration.



Member Feed: Real-time grid of submitted reports filtered by week and R&D area.



Report Editor: Technical documentation interface supporting rich text, video, and schematic (PDF) uploads.



Report Viewer: Distraction-free reading view with integrated media players and manager approval controls.



My Timeline: Personal history visualizing weekly submission consistency via a commit-graph style calendar.



Manager Dashboard: High-level telemetry of team output, area distribution, and pending approval queues.



Attendance Matrix: Cross-tabular view of member presence across lab sessions with low-frequency highlighting.



Access Control: Admin table for approving new members and assigning roles (Member, Manager, Advisor).



Key Flows

Weekly Report Submission: Hardware researcher submitting their weekly update.





User is on Member Feed -> sees global grid of recent reports



User clicks [New Report] -> opens Report Editor



User drafts content, uploads demo MP4, selects 'Projetos' area, clicks [Deploy]



Screen flashes cyan success toast -> redirects to Report Viewer with 'Pending Review' status



Design System

Color Palette





Primary: #00E5FF - Electric Cyan (CTAs, active states, focus rings)



Background: #0B0E14 - Deep Void (Page background)



Surface: #151A22 - Component Surface (Cards, sidebars, modals)



Text: #F1F5F9 - Bright Ash (Primary body, headings)



Muted: #475569 - Dimmed Slate (Borders, secondary text, placeholders)



Accent Success: #39FF14 - Neon Green (Approved badges, high attendance)



Accent Danger: #FF2442 - Laser Red (Missed reports, destructive actions)

Typography





Headings: Geist Mono, 600, 20-32px



Body: Geist Sans, 400, 14px



Data/Tags: Geist Mono, 500, 12px



Buttons: Geist Mono, 600, 13px, uppercase tracking

Style notes: 0px border radius everywhere. 1px solid borders (#475569) on all cards and inputs. Background features a subtle 24px grid pattern overlay at 3% opacity. Shadows are omitted in favor of solid borders and slight background color shifts (surface to surface-light).

